      "reviews": [
        {
          "reviewTitle": "Great everyday foundation",
          "reviewText": "This was my favorite foundation for a few years, though it\u2019s recently been dethroned by the new Victoria Beckham foundation drops. This is fragranced but they seem to have decreased it over time, so it stopped bothering me as a migraine-sensitive person. If anyone is comparing this to Clio kill cover mesh glow essential cushion (which has a strong peach fragrance that is borderline unbearable), Clio 23N Ginger is a hair lighter but it is comparable to the JSM 21W Medium\u2026 the puff applicator shape and the mesh delivery system in the Clio compact is much better, but the JSM foundation product itself is far superior in terms of how it melds with skin and makes it look. This is an excellent blurring foundation with light coverage that gives a nice, healthy glow to skin, but it will not necessarily cover darker imperfections like melasma or post-inflammatory hyperpigmentation. In the years that I\u2019ve used this, I found that the JSM Star-Cealer foundation in Light (the foundation and NOT the concealer that comes in the compact) did a better job of covering up spots with strong pigmentation I wanted to minimize. This product definitely needs a setting powder and it will cling to any dry patches\u2026 there are definitely times when I\u2019ve had to redo my skincare and makeup because I had some dry skin coming to the surface and hadn\u2019t exfoliated enough before applying it. You can still get some good coverage with this, but you need to be very careful about applying it in light layers and letting it sit for a time because too much and it can look cakey in certain lighting\u2026 I generally found it best to use the least amount of product in areas that the light hits (forehead, tops of cheekbones, etc) to ensure that it wouldn\u2019t look cakey once I applied setting powder and a little bronzer. I don\u2019t have large pores, but I found that if my base wasn\u2019t dry enough this could sometimes settle in my cheek pores in a way that made my skin looked textured\u2026 I am not sure if this foundation will work for someone who has significant textural variations, like pitted acne scarring. Because you only need a light layer of this product and it is thin in texture, it is more or less weightless and I\u2019ve never had it break me out. If you have skin that is generally in a good place without anything major to hide, this is an excellent light, perfecting foundation that WILL get you compliments on your skin. My other main criticisms of this is the shape of the applicator pad doesn\u2019t work well with crease areas like the sides of nostrils or corner of eues, in that it will usually deposit not enough or too much product in those spots. JSM does make some adorable fingertip cushion puffs that work well for these spots, but it would be much better if the applicator for this had some sort of point for better application to crevice areas. It\u2019s also sometimes difficult to use up all of the product, there will be a lot trapped in various parts of the sponge and you sort of need to press around for it and flip the sponge once in a while (which wastes a lot of product). I often wished I could just get this as some sort of drop product because otherwise I would need refills of this every month or two, I appreciate they sell pop-in refills, but sometimes they are really hard to get in/out of the compact (a few times I have needed to use actual tools to pop it out and all my body weight to get it in) and I hate the amount of plastic this is wasting over time. While the Clio compact design is ugly/bulky/tacky, I think JSM should take lessons from that product on how to modernize this compact\u2019s applicator and sponge delivery system\u2026 or just offer this in a drop foundation format. I did try the JSM liquid bottle foundation that was on the market a few years ago, but I found the heavy floral fragrance nauseating and it was a much thicker formula than whatever is in this compact. I think this is the best foundation you\u2019re going to find at this price point for someone who does not need full coverage and it\u2019s better than anything you\u2019re going to find at major beauty retails (U or S). I have repurchased it many times, but it could definitely use a little improvement.",
          "reviewDate": "Reviewed in the United States on March 9, 2026",
          "customer": "snowdrop",
          "customerProfileUrl": "https://www.amazon.com/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AEBFXBTR2RKNCXK5ZBP42E2TN4JQ",
          "customerStarsRating": 5,
          "productSpecs": {
            "size": "0.98 Fl Oz (Pack of 1)",
            "color": "[SPF] 21 Medium"
          },
          "helpfulVotes": "6 people found this helpful"
