        {
          "reviewTitle": "Cushion Foundation is a game changer!",
          "reviewText": "I love cushion foundation and Jung Saem Mool is a winner. It leaves my skin soft and natural looking while also providing good coverage of imperfections. The only downside was finding the perfect color. I tried three different mini compacts and finally settled on the 22N Peach Light. It\u2018s perfect for my complexion. Application is easy, I use a damp applicator for best results. I\u2018ve used it straight from the cushion but it doesn\u2019t give me the natural look I like. I\u2018m over 80 years old but have great skin that doesn\u2019t need heavy coverage. The cushion foundation doesn\u2019t settle in wrinkles if I use a damp applicator. I also follow my makeup application with a setting spray and it lasts all day. The only reason I gave it 4 stars instead of 5 is the problem I had finding the perfect color for my complexion.",
          "reviewDate": "Reviewed in the United States on November 16, 2025",
          "customer": "Suisseinpg",
          "customerProfileUrl": "https://www.amazon.com/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AHZWG2O5MPFFA5MD7GRIM4MJWGLQ",
          "customerStarsRating": 4,
          "productSpecs": {
            "size": "0.17 Fl Oz (Pack of 1)",
            "color": "22N Peach Light"
          },
          "helpfulVotes": "19 people found this helpful"
        },
        {
          "reviewTitle": "A \u201cMy-Skin-But-Better\u201d Cushion That Rarely Messes Up",
          "reviewText": "I\u2019ve tried more cushion foundations than I\u2019d like to admit, and this one earns its place in the daily rotation. The finish is what really stands out: natural, radiant, and skin-like. Not greasy, not flat, not \u201cI\u2019m clearly wearing makeup.\u201d It evens out tone beautifully, blurs pores in a very convincing way, and layers well if you need a bit more coverage without turning cakey. The texture is lightweight and comfortable, and my skin still feels normal hours later, not tight or suffocated. Application is almost foolproof. The mesh cushion and puff give you just the right amount of product, which makes it hard to overdo it. Great for rushed mornings and for people who don\u2019t want to think too hard about their base makeup. Now, to be fair, it\u2019s not perfect. If you\u2019re looking for full coverage or bulletproof all-day wear in heat and humidity, this isn\u2019t that cushion. T-zone can get a little shiny after several hours, and you may want to touch up. Also, I wouldn\u2019t call it \u201cskincare in a compact\u201d \u2014 it\u2019s more about great makeup than skin treatment. That said, if your goal is fresh, healthy-looking skin that doesn\u2019t scream foundation, this does the job extremely well. It\u2019s the kind of product that makes people ask, \u201cYour skin looks really good today,\u201d not \u201cWhat foundation are you wearing?\u201d Would definitely repurchase.",
          "reviewDate": "Reviewed in the United States on December 13, 2025",
          "customer": "Jason Lin",
          "customerProfileUrl": "https://www.amazon.com/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AEGJ7SOKMQTOFMTW22OCSOT7BVUA",
          "customerStarsRating": 5,
          "helpfulVotes": "10 people found this helpful"
